body:
“What are you doing?”

Eve’s heart skipped a beat. At first she thought it was Billie talking, but then she realized Billie would not speak with a Russian accent. It was Villanelle. Talking to her.

“Are you going to listen all night?”

Well, was she? Going to listen? She hadn’t really thought about how long she was going to sit here, but she knew that some part of her wanted to stay awake, wanted to hear from her again, wanted to know how she was doing. What she was doing.

“Are you having fun in Rome?”

Yes. Fuck, she was having fun. Because she was working with Villanelle. She had an excuse to spend time with her, listen to her, because it was all professional and what not. A justified excuse and an insane desire to protect her. An assassin.

Then Villanelle… giggled? And her breathing sounded so heavy.

Eve felt her heart beat even faster. It felt so damn intimate. The thought of Villanelle most likely lying in her bed, whispering to her, even though she knew she would not be able to get an answer… the thought excited Eve to no end. It allowed her to enjoy it. Shamelessly. Because she didn’t have to say anything. Couldn’t say anything. And yet here she was, at the receiving end, listening to the woman she desired.

And Villanelle sounded so… soft? Almost vulnerable. And so fucking, fucking sexy.

“You should let yourself go once in a while…”

Fuck, that accent… it was driving her insane. It sent shivers down her spine… having Villanelle’s voice literally inside her ear, so close… it was an intimacy she had never felt before.

“I can help you…”

Oh my god. Eve felt her pulse race. She was sure she had never wanted anyone this hard in her life.

And how much she wanted her to help her let go… How much she wanted to finally know what would happen if they dared go down that route.

Eve heard more heavy breathing. Was she… Was she actually doing that? Was Villanelle touching herself right this second? She had told her before that she’d masturbate thinking about Eve (often!), and Eve had had that image stuck inside her head ever since, but actually hearing her do it? It was a whole new level.

Eve felt that throbbing between her legs and she knew she had to do something about it. It was as if all her dirty little fantasies were coming true and Eve knew she had to take her chance. She was this close to just letting her hand slip inside her pants when she remembered there was somebody else in the room. Somebody who had made it quite clear that he was attracted to her.

Motivated by Villanelle’s heavy breathing she went over to the bed, straddling him.

“Don’t talk.”

Eve closed her eyes, trying her best to imagine Villanelle beneath her, wishing she would be even more vocal. She was craving the sound of her voice.

“You’re all I can think of.” – Oh, thank god. She’d keep talking, wouldn’t she?

“I think about the smell of your hair. About your skin. It felt so good to touch your hand today. I want to kiss your fingertips.”

Eve pressed her eyes shut, grinding against the man beneath her, concentrating on every soft moan coming from her earpiece.

“I’m so wet, Eve. Are you?”

Oh my fucking God.

“I’m about to push my fingers inside… and I’ll pretend they’re yours.”

Eve swallowed hard. She was fucking a man she wasn’t even attracted to, hushing him whenever he wanted to say something, and it was still the best sex she’d ever had. Because she wasn’t with him.

She was with her.

“I don’t think I can hold out for much longer, Eve.”

Eve picked up speed, she didn’t want Villanelle to come before her and there was no way to tell her to slow down.

Villanelle was moaning shamelessly now, but it didn’t sound cheap or forced. It felt like she wanted to let her know how much she desired her. How only the thought of Eve could drive her so wild.

Eve’s orgasm hit her hard, so hard that she had to bite her own fist to keep as quiet as possible.

And she wasn’t ready to open her eyes yet. She wasn’t ready to come back to reality.

“That was… satisfying.” Villanelle giggled again, followed by a long sigh.

“We should do this again sometime.”

Eve let herself sink down on the mattress beside him. He tried to kiss her neck and to snuggle up behind her.

“I don’t spoon”, Eve said quietly. Thank god he got the hint.

As much as she had enjoyed being the quiet listener in this scenario, Eve suddenly wished she could say something – anything – to Villanelle. She wanted to tell her that she was right. That she was jealous of these random girls.  That she wanted to talk to her about her personal life. Share things with her. Watch movies with her.

“Good night, Eve. Sweet dreams.”

Her voice was sincere. Soothing. Like a lullaby.

“Good night”, Eve whispered.

And she fell asleep with a smile on her face.

summary: villanelle wanting the shepherd's pie recipe to cook for eve is so funny and heartbreaking on one level bc she objectively has...
body:
villanelle wanting the shepherd’s pie recipe to cook for eve is so funny and heartbreaking on one level bc she objectively has no idea if eve actually does like it. villanelle’s perception is it’s incredibly important to her and to eve because it was the item that eve offered to her in 1x05 in this pivotal moment in their relationship. it’s seared in her memory of her first meeting (date) with eve. 

sitting down at the dinner table, eating a home cooked meal, having a conversation in the guise of what any normal, loving couple would do. knowing it was made by someone who presumably cares for eve and who eve cares for in return thus extracting the recipe from niko and (non-violently) remove any last ties he may have to eve. villanelle can take the figurative seat at the table with eve as a more permanent fixture. when she discovers he still chooses and loves eve, however, it shatters. the internal struggle between doing what she knows would have the most immediate, literal effect and the past experience with anna and genuinely attempting to navigate eve’s place within her own life and the consequences of her actions thereof…… it’s really all toooo much.
